                            <comment id="13980324" author="jensg" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2014 21:34:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have tested it using both trunk and 0.9.1 but it seems to work as expected. A line break within the string, as in your initial comment, produces a compiler error with both versions. Could you test with 0.9.1 again? Otherwise please add a sample thrift file that we can use to reproduce the problem. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13980367" author="vines" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2014 22:00:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tested with my source with 0.9.0 and now 0.9.1 and I&apos;m seeing the same behavior.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The important part of the java outputted is&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.quote = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;;

    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.escape = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;\\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;while the respective js is&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.quote = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;&quot;&apos;&lt;/span&gt;;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.escape = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;\&apos;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Between the two languages, it&apos;s inconsistent in how it treats escaping.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
